requiring copyright permission, other than copying as an exercise.

  "Propagate" means to do anything with the program that requires permission
under copyright law, except for private use.

  "Convey" means any kind of propagation that enables others to make
or receive copies.

  "Source code" means preferred form for making modifications, including
interface definitions and scripts to control compilation and installation.

  "Object code" means anything other than source code.

  "Appropriate Legal Entity" means a publicly-traded corporation, a partnership,
or nonprofit with no ownership by any one entity.

  "Installation Information" means any methods or procedures needed to install
and run modified versions of a covered work in a specific user-product.

