legal notices" and preserve existing interfaces.

  6. Conveying Non-Source Forms.

  You may convey a covered work in non-source form only under terms of section 4
and 5, and must provide the Corresponding Source.

  7. Additional Terms.

  Additional terms can be applied, but they must not conflict with this License.

  8. Termination.

  You may propagate or convey a covered work under conditions of this License
unless your rights have terminated.  If your rights have been terminated,
they are restored if conditions are met and you cure the violation.

  9. Acceptance Not Required for Having Copies.

  Mere possession and use do not require acceptance of this License.

  10. Automatic Licensing of Downstream Recipients.

  Each time you convey a covered work, recipients automatically receive a
license from the original licensors.

  11. Patents.

  A patent license is granted to all recipients of a covered work, as long
as you do not assert patents against others using the program.

  12. No Surrender of Others' Freedom.

  If conditions are imposed that require users of your covered work to
accept terms that restrict rights, those terms are void.

  13. Remote Network Interaction; Use with the GNU Affero General Public License.

  Conveying interactive access does not by itself trigger distribution.

